Cell[TextData[StyleBox["As you can see, there is a factor x[1,3] x[2,4] in \
the numerator, it will turn into x[1,2]x[3,4] after permutation, which is  u. \
In that case, we should get the subleading order of u in the expansion, or \
you can just remove this factor when 2<->3 happens. In that case, do not \
forget to multiple a v=1-Y, when 1<->2 happens. Here we use the version with \
x[1,2]x[3,4] multiplied, but for 1324 and 2314 we use numerator with \
x[1,2]x[3,4] removed, or you can understand it as there is one u removed, \
these are the O(u) results actually.",
 FontSize->18,
 FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0.5, 0]]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.986247924815213*^9, 3.986247967427717*^9}, {
  3.986248053936878*^9, 3.986248125652063*^9}, {3.986248163666062*^9, 
  3.986248180890704*^9}, {3.986248211764172*^9, 3.986248263193205*^9}, {
  3.986254295172013*^9, 
  3.986254414487623*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b40240f3-db97-40b4-a5c5-\
3841408ec3ac"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["For three loops, we only calculate above integrals to \
O(Y^3) and it finishes in seconds. Now we load them in order",
 FontSize->18]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.986248812018279*^9, 3.986248842135371*^9}, {
  3.9862489107958593`*^9, 
  3.986248915661331*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"817abbcc-af67-4292-ade1-\
8da23dec8e54"],

